{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1150,"text":"If I asked you to picture the air,"},{"time":5104,"text":"what do you imagine?"},{"time":8908,"text":"Most people think about either empty space"},{"time":12422,"text":"or clear blue sky"},{"time":14504,"text":"or sometimes trees dancing in the wind."},{"time":17849,"text":"And then I remember my high school\nchemistry teacher with really long socks"},{"time":21554,"text":"at the blackboard,"},{"time":22765,"text":"drawing diagrams of bubbles\nconnected to other bubbles,"},{"time":26193,"text":"and describing how they vibrate\nand collide in a kind of frantic soup."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32209,"text":"But really, we tend not to think\nabout the air that much at all."},{"time":36676,"text":"We notice it mostly"},{"time":38387,"text":"when there's some kind of unpleasant\nsensory intrusion upon it,"},{"time":42509,"text":"like a terrible smell\nor something visible like smoke or mist."},{"time":48131,"text":"But it's always there."},{"time":51207,"text":"It's touching all of us right now."},{"time":53711,"text":"It's even inside us."},{"time":57007,"text":"Our air is immediate, vital and intimate."},{"time":63063,"text":"And yet, it's so easily forgotten."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68009,"text":"So what is the air?"},{"time":70103,"text":"It's the combination of the invisible\ngases that envelop the Earth,"},{"time":73867,"text":"attracted by the Earth's\ngravitational pull."},{"time":77270,"text":"And even though I'm a visual artist,"},{"time":80720,"text":"I'm interested in\nthe invisibility of the air."},{"time":84627,"text":"I'm interested in how we imagine it,"},{"time":87226,"text":"how we experience it"},{"time":89298,"text":"and how we all have an innate\nunderstanding of its materiality"},{"time":93136,"text":"through breathing."},{"time":96530,"text":"All life on Earth changes the air\nthrough gas exchange,"},{"time":102214,"text":"and we're all doing it right now."},{"time":104679,"text":"Actually, why don't we all\nright now together take"},{"time":107671,"text":"one big, collective, deep breath in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110456,"text":"Ready? In. (Inhales)"},{"time":115009,"text":"And out. (Exhales)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":118782,"text":"That air that you just exhaled,"},{"time":121476,"text":"you enriched a hundred times\nin carbon dioxide."},{"time":126358,"text":"So roughly five liters of air per breath,\n17 breaths per minute"},{"time":132519,"text":"of the 525,600 minutes per year,"},{"time":138120,"text":"comes to approximately\n45 million liters of air,"},{"time":143604,"text":"enriched 100 times in carbon dioxide,"},{"time":147622,"text":"just for you."},{"time":149822,"text":"Now, that's equivalent to about 18\nOlympic-sized swimming pools."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156203,"text":"For me, air is plural."},{"time":158434,"text":"It's simultaneously\nas small as our breathing"},{"time":161531,"text":"and as big as the planet."},{"time":164689,"text":"And it's kind of hard to picture."},{"time":168587,"text":"Maybe it's impossible,\nand maybe it doesn't matter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171984,"text":"Through my visual arts practice,"},{"time":174617,"text":"I try to make air, not so much picture it,"},{"time":178334,"text":"but to make it visceral\nand tactile and haptic."},{"time":183177,"text":"I try to expand this notion\nof the aesthetic, how things look,"},{"time":188008,"text":"so that it can include things\nlike how it feels on your skin"},{"time":191645,"text":"and in your lungs,"},{"time":193367,"text":"and how your voice sounds\nas it passes through it."},{"time":198027,"text":"I explore the weight, density and smell,\nbut most importantly,"},{"time":202539,"text":"I think a lot about the stories we attach\nto different kinds of air."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210091,"text":"This is a work I made in 2014."},{"time":214872,"text":"It's called \"Different Kinds\nof Air: A Plant's Diary,\""},{"time":217995,"text":"where I was recreating the air\nfrom different eras in Earth's evolution,"},{"time":221927,"text":"and inviting the audience\nto come in and breathe them with me."},{"time":224951,"text":"And it's really surprising,\nso drastically different."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229845,"text":"Now, I'm not a scientist,"},{"time":231955,"text":"but atmospheric scientists\nwill look for traces"},{"time":234955,"text":"in the air chemistry in geology,"},{"time":237737,"text":"a bit like how rocks can oxidize,"},{"time":240078,"text":"and they'll extrapolate\nthat information and aggregate it,"},{"time":243451,"text":"such that they can\npretty much form a recipe"},{"time":246624,"text":"for the air at different times."},{"time":248709,"text":"Then I come in as the artist\nand take that recipe"},{"time":251368,"text":"and recreate it using the component gases."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256016,"text":"I was particularly interested\nin moments of time"},{"time":259770,"text":"that are examples\nof life changing the air,"},{"time":263836,"text":"but also the air that can influence\nhow life will evolve,"},{"time":268966,"text":"like Carboniferous air."},{"time":271579,"text":"It's from about 300 to 350\nmillion years ago."},{"time":275539,"text":"It's an era known\nas the time of the giants."},{"time":279321,"text":"So for the first time\nin the history of life,"},{"time":281809,"text":"lignin evolves."},{"time":283232,"text":"That's the hard stuff\nthat trees are made of."},{"time":285580,"text":"So trees effectively invent\ntheir own trunks at this time,"},{"time":289134,"text":"and they get really big,\nbigger and bigger,"},{"time":291204,"text":"and pepper the Earth,"},{"time":292583,"text":"releasing oxygen, releasing\noxygen, releasing oxygen,"},{"time":295900,"text":"such that the oxygen levels\nare about twice as high"},{"time":299538,"text":"as what they are today."},{"time":301601,"text":"And this rich air supports\nmassive insects --"},{"time":305488,"text":"huge spiders and dragonflies\nwith a wingspan of about 65 centimeters."},{"time":312369,"text":"To breathe, this air is really clean\nand really fresh."},{"time":316308,"text":"It doesn't so much have a flavor,"},{"time":318003,"text":"but it does give your body\na really subtle kind of boost of energy."},{"time":322499,"text":"It's really good for hangovers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":324390,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":326619,"text":"Or there's the air of the Great Dying --"},{"time":329317,"text":"that's about 252.5 million years ago,"},{"time":332965,"text":"just before the dinosaurs evolve."},{"time":335031,"text":"It's a really short time period,\ngeologically speaking,"},{"time":338787,"text":"from about 20- to 200,000 years."},{"time":341770,"text":"Really quick."},{"time":344175,"text":"This is the greatest extinction event\nin Earth's history,"},{"time":346891,"text":"even bigger than when\nthe dinosaurs died out."},{"time":350215,"text":"Eighty-five to 95 percent of species\nat this time die out,"},{"time":354196,"text":"and simultaneous to that is a huge,\ndramatic spike in carbon dioxide,"},{"time":359397,"text":"that a lot of scientists agree"},{"time":361014,"text":"comes from a simultaneous\neruption of volcanoes"},{"time":364175,"text":"and a runaway greenhouse effect."},{"time":368982,"text":"Oxygen levels at this time go\nto below half of what they are today,"},{"time":372609,"text":"so about 10 percent."},{"time":373928,"text":"So this air would definitely not\nsupport human life,"},{"time":376833,"text":"but it's OK to just have a breath."},{"time":378879,"text":"And to breathe, it's oddly comforting."},{"time":381939,"text":"It's really calming, it's quite warm"},{"time":384886,"text":"and it has a flavor a little bit\nlike soda water."},{"time":389058,"text":"It has that kind of spritz,\nquite pleasant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392925,"text":"So with all this thinking\nabout air of the past,"},{"time":395377,"text":"it's quite natural to start thinking\nabout the air of the future."},{"time":400142,"text":"And instead of being speculative with air"},{"time":402960,"text":"and just making up what I think\nmight be the future air,"},{"time":406498,"text":"I discovered this human-synthesized air."},{"time":410737,"text":"That means that it doesn't occur\nanywhere in nature,"},{"time":413742,"text":"but it's made by humans in a laboratory"},{"time":416883,"text":"for application in different\nindustrial settings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":421585,"text":"Why is it future air?"},{"time":423539,"text":"Well, this air is a really stable molecule"},{"time":427896,"text":"that will literally be part of the air\nonce it's released,"},{"time":431544,"text":"for the next 300 to 400 years,\nbefore it's broken down."},{"time":436274,"text":"So that's about 12 to 16 generations."},{"time":441433,"text":"And this future air has\nsome very sensual qualities."},{"time":445811,"text":"It's very heavy."},{"time":447779,"text":"It's about eight times heavier\nthan the air we're used to breathing."},{"time":453429,"text":"It's so heavy, in fact,\nthat when you breathe it in,"},{"time":456486,"text":"whatever words you speak\nare kind of literally heavy as well,"},{"time":459907,"text":"so they dribble down your chin\nand drop to the floor"},{"time":463137,"text":"and soak into the cracks."},{"time":465223,"text":"It's an air that operates\nquite a lot like a liquid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470047,"text":"Now, this air comes\nwith an ethical dimension as well."},{"time":474226,"text":"Humans made this air,"},{"time":476023,"text":"but it's also the most potent\ngreenhouse gas"},{"time":480303,"text":"that has ever been tested."},{"time":483042,"text":"Its warming potential is 24,000 times\nthat of carbon dioxide,"},{"time":488801,"text":"and it has that longevity\nof 12 to 16 generations."},{"time":493235,"text":"So this ethical confrontation\nis really central to my work."},{"time":511560,"text":"(In a lowered voice) It has\nanother quite surprising quality."},{"time":515483,"text":"It changes the sound of your voice\nquite dramatically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":518920,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":525145,"text":"So when we start to think -- ooh!\nIt's still there a bit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528161,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":529619,"text":"When we think about climate change,"},{"time":532233,"text":"we probably don't think about\ngiant insects and erupting volcanoes"},{"time":538226,"text":"or funny voices."},{"time":541207,"text":"The images that more readily come to mind"},{"time":543740,"text":"are things like retreating glaciers\nand polar bears adrift on icebergs."},{"time":549483,"text":"We think about pie charts\nand column graphs"},{"time":552363,"text":"and endless politicians\ntalking to scientists wearing cardigans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":558081,"text":"But perhaps it's time we start\nthinking about climate change"},{"time":562298,"text":"on the same visceral level\nthat we experience the air."},{"time":567738,"text":"Like air, climate change is simultaneously\nat the scale of the molecule,"},{"time":573202,"text":"the breath and the planet."},{"time":577139,"text":"It's immediate, vital and intimate,"},{"time":580642,"text":"as well as being amorphous and cumbersome."},{"time":586451,"text":"And yet, it's so easily forgotten."}]},{"cues":[{"time":591738,"text":"Climate change is the collective\nself-portrait of humanity."},{"time":595648,"text":"It reflects our decisions as individuals,"},{"time":598235,"text":"as governments and as industries."},{"time":601586,"text":"And if there's anything\nI've learned from looking at air,"},{"time":604852,"text":"it's that even though\nit's changing, it persists."},{"time":608785,"text":"It may not support the kind of life\nthat we'd recognize,"},{"time":612399,"text":"but it will support something."},{"time":615127,"text":"And if we humans are such a vital\npart of that change,"},{"time":618637,"text":"I think it's important\nthat we can feel the discussion."},{"time":623212,"text":"Because even though it's invisible,"},{"time":627285,"text":"humans are leaving\na very vibrant trace in the air."}]},{"cues":[{"time":632991,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634231,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}